The deadly Camp Fire in California spread rapidly, with fire spotters unable to stop it. Firetrucks and helicopters were unable to reach the blaze due to timing and weather conditions. The fire quickly destroyed towns and claimed numerous structures and lives. President Donald Trump and the author of the op-ed witnessed the devastation during their recent trips to California. They also witnessed the bravery of firefighters, first responders, and volunteers working together to combat the fire and assist the community.